						               													<description>A board game without dice, based in risk control and strategy. With a duration of 30-60 min, in &amp;ldquo;Infernis&amp;rdquo; 2 to 4 players take the role of as many witches challenging each other in a cruel game of magic and cunning.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Essentially, it consists in a large square plain with parcels that contain magic and form a grid. When this magic is activated, an arcane wind blows the occupant following different directions and with variable strength (and, subsequently, range). These blows, along with the witch-players&amp;rsquo; ability to control or anticipate them, will determine whether the peasants stay on the island long enough or they are thrown into the deadly flames.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Only the witch that manages to keep her unlucky peasants alive will win, preventing them from falling in the eternal flames that surround the cursed island of Infernis.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
